2546172.name: 4140 Green detection instead of Brown detection
2546172.title: 4140 Green detection instead of Brown detection
2546172.subject: Henan Haoyu company Detection Systems
2546172.findtext: 2546172 4140 done Henan Haoyu company Omnia FT-250 / FT-330 Detection Systems Nick van den Brink Mike Burgers 4140 Green detection instead of Brown detection Henan Haoyu company Detection Systems Omnia FT-250 / FT-330
2546172.filterfields: {"idx":"4140","Customer":"Henan Haoyu company","Machine":"Omnia FT-250 / FT-330","Maingroup":"Detection Systems","FromName":"Nick van den Brink"}

About.value: Customer is willing to buy an Omnia FT-250, on 1 condition: we need to be able to sort the different 'shades' of green eggs.

Happen.value:
Investigate the possibility and costs to adapt the Blood/Brown detector to scan green eggs in the same way as we currently clasify brown eggs in a number of different levels
As with the current brown detection, it must be possible to grade the eggs according to their green colour. White eggs should have their own clasification too.

Consider.value: Customer uses 99% green eggs and 1% white eggs. < in the same batch?>

Problems.value: DOS environment causes restrictions in software capabilities, meaning the solution must work, but a rather quick and dirty solution is acceptable.

Expect.value: If possible, we expect a solution that can grade green eggs on colour, similar to the capabilities of the brown detection. We also expect a clear description with regard to the conditions under which this functionality can operate.

Subject.value: Green detection instead of Brown detection

Master.value: 4140 Green detection instead of Brown detection
